  <!-- Legal Powers & Framework -->
  <section class="legal-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">Legal Powers &amp; Framework</h2>
          <p class="section-sub">The legislation that gives LCC and the Secretary of State power to control roadworks, charge for disruption, and enforce compliance</p>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="legal-grid">
          <div class="legal-card legal-card-primary">
            <div class="legal-icon">&#9878;</div>
            <h3>Network Management Duty</h3>
            <p class="legal-cite">Traffic Management Act 2004, s16-17</p>
            <p>Every local traffic authority <strong>must</strong> manage their road network to secure expeditious movement of traffic. LCC must consider the needs of <em>all road users</em> including pedestrians, cyclists, and public transport.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-card">
            <div class="legal-icon">&#128176;</div>
            <h3>Lane Rental Charges</h3>
            <p class="legal-cite">TMA 2004, s74A &bull; SI 2012/3073</p>
            <p>Up to <strong>&pound;2,500/day</strong> charged to utilities for occupying traffic-sensitive roads during peak hours. Currently operating in London, Kent, Surrey, and Sussex. LCC is actively exploring adoption.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-card">
            <div class="legal-icon">&#9200;</div>
            <h3>Overrun Charges (s74)</h3>
            <p class="legal-cite">NRSWA 1991, s74 &bull; SI 2025/1074</p>
            <p>Up to <strong>&pound;10,000/day</strong> on traffic-sensitive roads when works overrun the agreed duration. From January 2026, charges now apply on <strong>weekends and bank holidays</strong> too.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-card">
            <div class="legal-icon">&#128203;</div>
            <h3>Permit Scheme</h3>
            <p class="legal-cite">TMA 2004, s37 &bull; SI 2007/3372</p>
            <p>Lancashire Permit Scheme requires all utility works to obtain a permit before starting. Conditions can specify <strong>timing, methods, and traffic management</strong>. Working without a permit: <strong>&pound;500 fixed penalty</strong>.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-card">
            <div class="legal-icon">&#128337;</div>
            <h3>Timing Directions (s56)</h3>
            <p class="legal-cite">NRSWA 1991, s56</p>
            <p>LCC can direct utility companies to carry out works at <strong>specific times or on specific days</strong> where works would cause serious disruption. Underused power that could force overnight working on critical corridors.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-card">
            <div class="legal-icon">&#128683;</div>
            <h3>Resurfacing Embargoes</h3>
            <p class="legal-cite">NRSWA 1991, s58-58A</p>
            <p>After substantial road resurfacing, LCC can <strong>restrict further excavation for up to 3 years</strong> (5 years on new roads). This prevents the costly cycle of &ldquo;dig-fill-dig&rdquo; on recently repaired surfaces.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-card">
            <div class="legal-icon">&#128200;</div>
            <h3>Fixed Penalty Notices</h3>
            <p class="legal-cite">NRSWA 1991, s95A-D &bull; SI 2025/1074</p>
            <p>FPNs <strong>doubled from &pound;120 to &pound;240</strong> from 5 January 2026 for permit breaches and notice failures. Working without a permit now attracts a <strong>&pound;500 FPN</strong>. Strong financial incentive for compliance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-card">
            <div class="legal-icon">&#127970;</div>
            <h3>Protected Streets</h3>
            <p class="legal-cite">NRSWA 1991, s61 &bull; TMA 2004 s36A</p>
            <p>LCC can designate streets where no works may be carried out without specific permission. Used for <strong>high-footfall town centres</strong> and critical transport corridors.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Options Appraisal -->
  {trafficData.congestion_model?.options_appraisal?.length > 0 && (
