  <!-- Major Roads Guide -->
  <section class="roads-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">Burnley&rsquo;s Road Network</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">
            The major routes through and around Burnley, what they connect, and known issues
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="roads-accordions">
          <Accordion title="M65 Motorway (Junctions 9, 10, 11)" defaultOpen={true}>
            <div class="road-detail">
              <div class="road-meta">
                <span class="road-tag">Motorway</span>
                <span class="road-maintainer">National Highways (J1-10) / LCC (J10-14)</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                The M65 runs east-west across Lancashire from the M6 near Preston through Blackburn,
                Accrington, and Burnley, ending at Colne. Burnley is served by three junctions:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Junction 9</strong> &mdash; Rosegrove. Access to Accrington Road, Rossendale Road, and south Burnley. Connects to the A679.</li>
                <li><strong>Junction 10</strong> &mdash; Burnley Barracks Interchange. The main junction for Burnley town centre via Cavalry Way. A large two-island roundabout spanning 500 metres. Known air quality exceedance area.</li>
                <li><strong>Junction 11</strong> &mdash; Barracks/Brierfield. Access to north Burnley and Brierfield via the A6114.</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="road-issue">
                <strong>Safety concerns:</strong> A series of fatal crashes in 2024 prompted calls for an urgent safety review
                of the M65 between Junctions 5 and 14. A multi-vehicle collision at Junction 9 in October 2024
                killed one person. Much of the M65 is unlit east of Blackburn. National Highways completed
                an &pound;84M safety programme in 2004 but concerns persist.
              </div>
            </div>
          </Accordion>

          <Accordion title="A56 (Burnley to Manchester)">
            <div class="road-detail">
              <div class="road-meta">
                <span class="road-tag">A-Road</span>
                <span class="road-maintainer">National Highways / LCC</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                Runs south from Burnley as a dual carriageway, skirting the western edge of the town.
                Links to the M66 motorway heading toward Manchester and the M62. This is the primary
                north-south route connecting Burnley to Greater Manchester and is heavily used by commuters.
              </p>
            </div>
          </Accordion>

          <Accordion title="A671 (Cavalry Way / through Padiham)">
            <div class="road-detail">
              <div class="road-meta">
                <span class="road-tag">A-Road</span>
                <span class="road-maintainer">LCC</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                Runs south from Bacup over Deerplay Moor into Burnley, crossing the A646 at the town
                centre. North of Burnley it becomes a primary road at M65 Junction 10 (Cavalry Way),
                then passes through Padiham as Main Street, bypasses Whalley, and ends at the A59.
              </p>
              <div class="road-issue">
                <strong>Air quality:</strong> A 271-metre section at Junction 10 exceeds annual NO2 limits.
                43% of nitrogen oxides come from cars. The large motorway junction with two traffic islands
                is a known bottleneck causing idling traffic.
              </div>
            </div>
          </Accordion>

          <Accordion title="A679 (Accrington Road / Burnley Road, Hapton)">
            <div class="road-detail">
              <div class="road-meta">
                <span class="road-tag">A-Road</span>
                <span class="road-maintainer">LCC</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                Connects Burnley westward to Accrington via Hapton. Speed enforcement operates on the
                30mph section at Hapton. The junction with Rossendale Road and Liverpool Road near
                M65 Junction 9 (Rosegrove junction) is a known congestion hotspot, widened in a
                12-month project in 2019-2020 but still regularly disrupted by utility works and
                housing development traffic.
              </p>
            </div>
          </Accordion>

          <Accordion title="A646 (Todmorden Road / Rossendale Road)">
            <div class="road-detail">
              <div class="road-meta">
                <span class="road-tag">A-Road</span>
                <span class="road-maintainer">LCC</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                Runs south-east from Burnley town centre toward Todmorden and West Yorkshire through
                the Cliviger Gorge. A key cross-Pennine route carrying significant HGV traffic.
                The road follows the River Calder valley and is prone to flooding in heavy rainfall.
              </p>
            </div>
          </Accordion>

          <Accordion title="A682 (Centenary Way / to Rawtenstall and Nelson)">
            <div class="road-detail">
              <div class="road-meta">
                <span class="road-tag">A-Road</span>
                <span class="road-maintainer">LCC</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                Runs south to Rawtenstall through Rossendale and north-east to Nelson and the
                Yorkshire Dales. This road is carried through Burnley town centre on the
                <strong>Centenary Way Viaduct</strong>, a seven-span continuous bridge that underwent
                a &pound;1.65M refurbishment in 2015-16, addressing chloride-induced concrete damage
                from decades of de-icing salt, bearing replacement, expansion joints, and deck waterproofing.
              </p>
            </div>
          </Accordion>

          <Accordion title="Key Local Roads">
            <div class="road-detail">
              <div class="local-roads-grid">
                <div class="local-road">
                  <h4>Padiham Road</h4>
                  <p>One of Burnley&rsquo;s oldest routes connecting to Padiham, Whalley, and Blackburn. Currently subject to a TTRO for improvement works.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="local-road">
                  <h4>Manchester Road</h4>
                  <p>Key gateway into Burnley from the south. Currently under one-way system for the &pound;55M Levelling Up programme. Severe congestion reported.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="local-road">
                  <h4>Colne Road</h4>
                  <p>Major improvements underway (Jan&ndash;Aug 2026). Two-way signals during construction. New average speed cameras installed.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="local-road">
                  <h4>Briercliffe Road</h4>
                  <p>Connects Burnley northeast to Briercliffe village. Subject to emergency traffic regulation orders for maintenance.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="local-road">
                  <h4>Barden Lane</h4>
                  <p>Local road identified as severely affected by concurrent roadworks. Active TTRO near Lower Manor Lane junction.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="local-road">
                  <h4>Brunshaw Road / Brunshaw Avenue</h4>
                  <p>Listed for resurfacing work from Brunshaw Road to Redlees Road, plus surface dressing.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Accordion>
