  <!-- How to Get a Pothole Fixed -->
  <section class="pothole-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">How to Get a Pothole Fixed</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">
            The process, the timescales, and what to do if nothing happens
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pothole-steps stagger-children">
          <div class="pothole-step">
            <span class="step-number">1</span>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h3>Report It</h3>
              <p>
                Report the pothole on the
                <a href="https://www.lancashire.gov.uk/roads-parking-and-travel/report-it/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LCC website</a>
                or call 0300 123 6780. Include the exact location, size, and a photo if possible.
                You&rsquo;ll get a reference number.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pothole-step">
            <span class="step-number">2</span>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h3>It Gets Assessed</h3>
              <p>
                LCC uses a risk-based assessment. Potholes deeper than 40mm on a carriageway are classed as
                &ldquo;safety defects&rdquo; and should be repaired within 20 working days (Cat 2) or 2 hours
                if they pose an immediate danger (Cat 1). Smaller defects go on the planned maintenance programme.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pothole-step">
            <span class="step-number">3</span>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h3>The Repair</h3>
              <p>
                Reform&rsquo;s approach has shifted to larger, more permanent repairs: averaging 6m&sup2; per repair
                (up from 2m&sup2;) at under &pound;100/m&sup2; (down from &pound;200/m&sup2;). The goal is
                fewer repeat visits to the same location.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pothole-step">
            <span class="step-number">4</span>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h3>If Nothing Happens</h3>
              <p>
                If the repair isn&rsquo;t done within the target timescale, you have three options:
                chase it via your LCC reference number, report it again on FixMyStreet (which creates
                a public record), or <a href="/contact/">contact me directly</a> and I will chase the
                highways department on your behalf.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pothole-data-note">
          <strong>Data problem:</strong> LCC&rsquo;s HAMS asset management system is being decommissioned,
          which means the council currently cannot verify whether it is meeting its own pothole repair targets.
          This is being addressed but it means published repair statistics should be treated with caution.
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

